# ADR-078 Continuity

- Read in order before implementing: `AGENTS.md`, `docs/SESSION-HANDOFF.md`, `docs/CHANGELOG.md`, `docs/ADR/078-consolidated-follow-through-program.md`, `docs/ARCHITECTURE.md`, `docs/API-BOUNDARY.md`, `docs/DATA-MODEL.md`, `docs/TEST-PLAN.md`, then any ADRs referenced by the chosen step.
- Treat `docs/ADR/078-consolidated-follow-through-program.md` as the source of truth for the active continuation backlog and execution order.
- Treat `docs/SESSION-HANDOFF.md` as the source of truth for the latest completed checkpoint and next step.
- Treat `docs/CHANGELOG.md` as the source of truth for what has actually landed.
- If ADR, handoff, changelog, and code disagree, stop and reconcile docs before code changes.
- One session = one bounded active item or tightly coupled sub-item from ADR-078. Do not expand scope or skip the documented order.
- At session start, identify the highest-priority unfinished ADR-078 item whose dependencies are satisfied and restate: current item, purpose, likely affected files/modules, and what is out of scope.
- Keep the final architecture fully PersAI-native. Do not preserve OpenClaw request-time compatibility in target-state code.
- Do not keep `openclawBootstrap` / `openclawWorkspace` as long-term runtime truth. Do not reintroduce filesystem-owned session state. Do not put sandbox or heavy agent boot into the ordinary chat path.
- Touch native OpenClaw only if historical analysis explicitly requires it and a PersAI-side change is insufficient.
- `Step 15a` is cancelled. Do not reopen it unless the founder explicitly creates a new ADR or asks for a fresh architecture decision.
- Before ending the session, update `docs/SESSION-HANDOFF.md`, update `docs/CHANGELOG.md` if repo truth changed, update ADR-078 if architecture or active backlog changed, and state the next recommended step.
